  <div class="center-text">
    Grace Jordan-Weinstein
  </div>
  <p>I’m a second year at Northwestern University studying Journalism in the Medill School. I’m from Philadelphia but have loved exploring Chicago in my free time. I am the styling director for STITCH, Northwestern’s fashion magazine, as well as writing film reviews for The Daily Northwestern and Dj-ing for WNUR’s rock and jazz shows. I’m also a part of the Northwestern Crew Team. Below is a map of all the places I’ve rowed with NU Crew.</p>
  <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=15U1V3ISQ1QdWSYu6Xh2wVpVoazeOrFw&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1" width="640" height="480"></iframe>
  <div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 5px solid black; width: 80%; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: bold;">Music</h1>
  <p1>For as long as I can remember, music has been a driving and structuring passion in my life, both in the classroom and in my extracurricular life. At Northwestern University, I hostboth the Rock and Jazz shows at WNUR, the university’s radio station, incorporating music into my week as a time to appreciate great artistry amidst a rigorous academic calendar. As a DJ, I am involved in all aspects of making the radio programs happen, from on-air broadcasting to creating programming, and operating soundboards. Finally, from a personal standpoint, I am an avid vinyl collector and try to attend concerts in Chicago whenever I can. </p1>
  <div class="line-container">
    <hr class="line">
  </div>
  <h2>My top 100 songs!</h2>
  <p2>Though I’ve eschewed the type of ranking publications like Pitchfork or Rolling Stone typically does, I’ve gathered what are, in my opinion, the 100 best songs.

    I’ve decided to keep the options to “pop music” — which I am classifying as most music that's not jazz, classical or showtunes.
    </p2>
